{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}} [[File:Estelada blava.svg|thumb|right|190px|"L'Estelada Blava" (''The Blue Starred Flag''), the blue version of the pro-independence flag]] [[File:Estelada roja.svg|thumb|right|190px|"L'Estelada Vermella" (''The Red Starred Flag''), the red version of the pro-independence flag]]
{{Wikisource|Declaration to start the independence process of Catalonia}} After pro-independence parties won a majority of seats in the [[Catalonia|Catalan]] election on 27 September 2015, the '''Declaration of the Initiation of the Process of Independence of Catalonia''' ({{lang-ca|Declaració d'inici del procés d'independència de Catalunya}}) was issued on 9 November 2015. The declaration declares the start of the process to create an [[Catalan Republic|independent Catalan state]] in the form of a [[republic]] and proclaims the start of a participative, open, integrating and active citizens' constituent process to lay the foundation for the future [[Catalan constitutions|Catalan Constitution]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Parliament declares the start of the independence process|url=http://www.catalannewsagency.com/politics/item/the-parliament-declares-the-start-of-the-independence-process|publisher=Catalan News Agency|date=9 November 2015|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Catalonia launches process of separation from Spain|url=http://english.vilaweb.cat/noticies/catalonia-launches-process-of-separation-from-spain/|publisher=VilaWeb|date=9 November 2015|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Catalonia's parliament votes to begin setting up an independent state|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/spain/11984516/Catalonias-parliament-votes-to-begin-setting-up-an-independent-state.html|publisher=The Telegraph|date=9 November 2015|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= In Catalonia, the Independence Process Begins|url=https://www.stratfor.com/analysis/catalonia-independence-process-begins|publisher=Stratfor|date=9 November 2015|accessdate=10 November 2015}}</ref>
The declaration was passed with 72 votes in favor, 63 against and 0 abstentions in the [[Parliament of Catalonia]].
On 9 June 2017, the Catalan government announced the date of the [[Catalan independence referendum, 2017|independence referendum]]. It was declared illegal on 6 September 2017 and suspended by the [[Constitutional Court of Spain]] because it breached the [[Spanish Constitution of 1978]].<ref name="boe2162017">{{cite web|url=https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2017/09/08/pdfs/BOE-A-2017-10287.pdf|title=Recurso de inconstitucionalidad n.º 4334-2017, contra la Ley del Parlamento de Cataluña 19/2017, de 6 de septiembre, del Referéndum de Autodeterminación.|publisher=Agencia Estatal Boletín Oficial del Estado|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=5 October 2017|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-09-10/catalan-separatists-plot-show-of-strength-in-battle-with-madrid|title=Catalan Separatists Plot Show of Force in Battle With Madrid|last=Duarte|first=Esteban|date=11 September 2017|work=Bloomberg|accessdate=13 September 2017|language=en}}</ref> It was held on 1 October the same year, using a disputed voting process,<ref name="ElPais03102017">{{cite web|url=https://elpais.com/elpais/2017/10/01/inenglish/1506858911_482600.html|title=Did the referendum comply with basic voting regulations?|date=3 October 2017|publisher=[[El País]]|accessdate=5 October 2017 }}</ref><ref name="TheIndependent02102017">{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/catalan-independence-referendum-not-legal-spanish-constitution-european-commission-juncker-spain-law-a7978386.html|title=The EU Commission just said the Catalan referendum was illegal|last=|first=|date=2 October 2017|work=<nowiki>`[The Independent]]</nowiki>|accessdate=4 October 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/happened-catalonias-vote-independence-whats-next/|title=What happened with Catalonia's vote for independence -- and what's next|last=Epatko|first=Larisa|date=4 October 2017|work=[[PBS NewsHour]]|accessdate=4 October 2017|archive-url=|archivedate=|dead-url=}}</ref> resulting in a 90% majority of votes favouring independence with a turnout of 42.58%.<ref>The Guardian, [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/oct/01/dozens-injured-as-riot-police-storm-catalan-ref-polling-stations Catalan referendum: preliminary results show 90% in favour of independence], 2 October 2017</ref> Subsequently the [[European Commission]] agreed that the referendum was illegal.<ref name="TheIndependent02102017" />
