{{Infobox museum | name = '''Kgosi Sechele I Museum''' | native_name = | native_name_lang = [[Setswana]] | image = Sechele_Gustav_Fritsch_1865.jpg | caption = [[Sechele I|Kgosi Sechele]] Botswana Legacy (Kgosi Sechele Museum I is named after him.) | alt = | map_type = | map_caption = | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|24|24|24|S|25|29|42|E|region:za}} | established = 1902 | dissolved = | location = [[Molepolole]], [[Botswana]] | type = | collection = Cultural preservation | visitors = | director = | president = | curator = | publictransit = | network = | website = [[List of museums in Botswana]] }} The '''Kgosi Sechele I Museum''' is a national [[museum]] located in [[Molepolole]], [[Botswana]].The museum was founded in 1902 and was made open to the public in 1992.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kgosisechele.com/about-us/|title=Establishment of Kgosi Sechele Museum (Molepolole)|last=Sechele|first=Kgosi|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=30 November 2017}}</ref> Highlights include much [[memorabilia]] relating to the famous explorer [[David Livingstone]] (1813 to 1873).
== History == Kgosi Sechele Museum prseserves and promotes the culture of [[Botswana]]. It was founded in 1902 and had its building being constructed by the kweneng district people of [[Molepolole]]. The construction is made in the old historical buildings and was declared open to the public in 1992 and also a national museum.
