{{short description|Travel planning guide provided by AAA}} {{Multiple issues|{{undue weight|date=November 2018}}{{advert|date=November 2018}}}}
'''Trip Tik''' is a [[Guide book|travel planning guide]] provided by [[American Automobile Association|AAA]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/vacation-planning-before-google-maps-1438124862|title=Vacation-Planning Before Google Maps|last=Greene|first=Bob|date=2015-07-28|work=Wall Street Journal|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en-US|issn=0099-9660}}</ref> It provides travelers with destination directions, points of interest, and services which are customised for the user.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/design/2015-05-20/summer-fun-roadtripping-aaa-style/|title=Summer Fun: Roadtripping, AAA-style|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref> The Trip Tik facility was first made available to AAA members in 2000.<ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://www.esri.com/news/arcnews/fall02articles/aaa-triptik.html|title=Esri News -- ArcNews Fall 2002 Issue -- AAA's TripTik/Traveler Rated "The Best Cartographer"|website=www.esri.com|access-date=2018-09-19}}</ref> It came in printed booklet version but is now available in desktop and mobile versions.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.omaha.com/money/aaa-s-triptik-is-still-cruising-even-in-the-google/article_0f525d2a-4d2e-5323-b224-7a07066e8447.html|title=AAA's TripTik is still cruising, even in the Google Maps age|last=writer|first=Janice Podsada / World-Herald staff|work=Omaha.com|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.autoguide.com/auto-news/2010/10/free-aaa-triptik-app-offers-directions-and-much-more.html|title=Free AAA TripTik App Offers Directions and Much More » AutoGuide.com News|date=2010-10-28|work=AutoGuide.com|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref> The map is free for AAA members.<ref name=":1" /> A Trip Tik [[mobile app]] is available for [[iOS]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.aol.com/2010/07/09/aaa-triptik-app-doesnt-compare-to-old-fashioned-paper-triptiks/|title=AAA TripTik app doesn't compare to old fashioned paper TripTiks|last=Staff|first=AOL|work=AOL.com|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":2" /> The digital version provides all traveler requirements in one page including navigation.<ref name=":0" />
== Map features ==
* It has a scrolling list of point of interest list which has AAA approved hotels, restaurants, attractions, etc.<ref name=":2" /> * There are filters which have options to highlight hotels, attractions, restaurants, gas stations, construction, detour routes, etc.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lombardihonda.com/en/blog/plan-your-vacation-with-caas-triptik/2184.html|title=Plan your vacation with CAA's TripTik {{!}} Lombardi Honda|website=lombardihonda.com|access-date=2018-09-19}}</ref><ref name=":3" /> * Websites for rentals booking etc. will be redirected from inside the map.<ref name=":0" /> In certain cases descriptions and reviews are made available on the same page.<ref name=":0" /> * Provides the cost of gas at different gas stations.<ref name=":0" /> * Also provides other facilities such as weather, traffic, etc. in the same map.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://skift.com/2015/05/22/the-most-successful-trip-planning-app-still-comes-in-a-paper-version/|title=The Most Successful Trip Planning App Still Comes in a Paper Version|date=2015-05-22|work=Skift|access-date=2018-09-19|language=en-US}}</ref>
